properties.areaDesc: Two Rivers to Sheboygan WI; Rock Island Passage to Sturgeon Bay WI; Sturgeon Bay to Two Rivers WI
properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued February 14 at 10:39AM CST until February 15 at 9:00PM CST by NWS Green Bay WI
properties.description:
* WHAT...Southwest winds increasing to 15 to 25 knots with gusts
up to 30 knots. A few gale force gusts to 35 knots possible.
Waves of 4 to 7 feet this evening building to 6 to 10 feet by
midnight.

* WHERE...Lake Michigan nearshore waters from Rock Island Passage
to Sheboygan WI.

* WHEN...From 9 PM this evening to 9 PM CST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Freezing spray is likely tonight through
Saturday morning. The freezing spray could be heavy.
properties.instruction:
Inexperienced mariners, especially those operating smaller
vessels, should avoid navigating in hazardous conditions.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 9 PM THIS EVENING TO 9 PM CST SATURDAY
